race.comment: MAGICAL MOMENTS (8) settled near the tail then wound up nicely to grab fourth when resuming over 1200m at this track last start. Placed at both runs over 1400m so with that first-up run out of the way she looks ready to make her mark. BRUNDEE TOM (6) came with a powerful finish to collect his maiden win recently over this distance at the Sapphire Coast. Gets a soft run out of gate one and although this is much tougher he should be competitive. EASIEST CHOICE (3) started warm favourite and easily won at 1300m Newcastle maiden when returning from a 200-day spell last start. Lightly raced mare with plenty more in store. DAMASCUS CALLING (4) has been about the mark at his last couple and should be cherry ripe now at the fourth run back. TSAREVICH (2) returned from a five-month spell and was lining up for just the second time when a barnstorming winner over 1300m at this track. Promising three-year-old who should cope with this class rise.
